verbs.description: disbecome (third-person singular simple present disbecomes, present participle disbecoming, simple past disbecame, past participle disbecome)

entries.meaning: (obsolete, transitive) To misbecome; to fail to suit; to be unfitting.
examples: be careful That your compassion of my age, nor his, Move you to any thing that may disbecome The place on which you sit
